ROAD improvement work is due to start in the next few weeks. Roadworks warning ROAD improvement work is due to start in the next few weeks.The East Shaw Street and Sir Michael Street roundabouts in Greenock, will be the latest road surfaces to benefit from an ongoing investment programme.Improvements are needed as the road surface is reaching the end of its operational life. The work will start at a weekend - on Sunday September 21 - to minimise the disruption it will cause to local businesses. 